{"task_url":"https://www.codechef.com/IARCSJUD/problems/TILINGS","statement":{"HTML":{"html":"\n<html>\n\t<head>\n\t\t<link rel=\"stylesheet\" href=\"https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/github-markdown-css/3.0.1/github-markdown.min.css\">\n\t\t<script type=\"text/x-mathjax-config\">\n\t\t\tMathJax.Hub.Config({\n\t\t\t\ttex2jax: {inlineMath: [['$','$']]}\n\t\t\t});\n\t\t</script>\n\t\t<script src='https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/mathjax/2.7.5/MathJax.js?config=TeX-MML-AM_CHTML' async></script>\n\t\t<style>\n\t\t\t.markdown-body {\n\t\t\t\tbackground-color: white;\n\t\t\t\tpadding-bottom: 20px;\n\t\t\t}\n\t\t\t.markdown-body code {\n\t\t\t\tcolor: #24292e;\n\t\t\t}\n\t\t\t.solution-visible-txt {\n\t\t\t\tdisplay: none;\n\t\t\t}\n\t\t</style>\n\t</head>\n\t<body class=\"markdown-body\">\n\t\t<h1>Number of Tilings</h1>\n<p>You have to tile a room that is two units wide and $N$ units long. You have with you two types of tiles: a rectangle that is one unit wide and two units long, and an L-shaped tile covering three square units. Here are pictures of the two types of tiles.</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://codechef_shared.s3.amazonaws.com/download/Images/IARCSJUD/TILINGS/fig1.png\" alt=\"1-1\" title=\"Figure 1\" /></p>\n<p>You are allowed to rotate the tiles when you lay them. You have an infinite supply of both types of tiles. Your objective is to calculate the number of different ways of tiling the room using these tiles.</p>\n<p>For instance, a $2 \\times 3$ room can be tiled in $5$ different ways, as follows:</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://codechef_shared.s3.amazonaws.com/download/Images/IARCSJUD/TILINGS/fig2.png\" alt=\"1-2\" title=\"Figure 2\" /></p>\n<p>Notice that a tiling can use both types of tiles. Consider, for instance, the following tiling of a $2 \\times 4$ room.</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://codechef_shared.s3.amazonaws.com/download/Images/IARCSJUD/TILINGS/fig3.png\" alt=\"1-3\" title=\"Figure 3\" /></p>\n<p>Given $N$, your task is to determine the number of ways to tile a room of size $2×N$. Since this number may be very large, it is sufficient to report the last four digits of the answer. For instance the number of ways to tile a $2 \\times 13$ room is $13465$. Your program should just print $3465$. If the answer involves fewer than $4$ digits then print the entire answer. For example, if $N$ = 3 you should print $5$.</p>\n<h3>Input:</h3>\n<p>A single integer $N$, indicating the size of the room.</p>\n<h3>Output:</h3>\n<p>The last four digits of the number of ways of tiling the $2×N$ room. If the answer involves fewer than $4$ digits, print the entire answer.</p>\n<h3>Constraints</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>$ 1 \\leq N \\leq 1000000$.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Sample Input</h3>\n<pre><code>13\n</code></pre>\n<h3>Sample Output</h3>\n<pre><code>3465\n</code></pre>\n<aside style='background: #f8f8f8;padding: 10px 15px;'><div>All submissions for this problem are available.</div></aside>\n\t<body>\n</html>"}}}